The following module structure is in section 2.2 of the language specification, but this currently fails if I try to use the X.Y.Z interface with the error "The property 'Z' does not exist on value of type 'X.Y'."

I presume this is an error in the compiler.

Demo: http://www.typescriptlang.org/Playground/#src=module%20X%20{%0A%09export%20module%20Y%20{%0A%09%09export%20interface%20Z%20{%20%0A%09%09%09%0A%09%09}%0A%09}%0A%09export%20interface%20Y%20{%20%0A%0A%09}%0A}%0A%0Avar%20z%3A%20X.Y.Z%3B

```
module X {
	export module Y {
		export interface Z { 
			
		}
	}
	export interface Y { 

	}
}

var z: X.Y.Z;
```
